{{Infobox scientist |name = Daniel Larimer |native_name = |image = |image_size = |caption = |birth_date = |birth_place = |residence = [[Christiansburg, Virginia|Christiansburg]], [[Virginia]]<ref name="roanoke">{{cite news |last1=Demmitt |first1=Jacob |title=Empty walls and big ambitions: Inside block.one, the $1.5 billion cryptocurrency startup taking shape in Blacksburg |url=https://www.roanoke.com/news/local/blacksburg/empty-walls-and-big-ambitions-inside-block-one-the-billion/article_7cd01db6-2a1b-11e8-bf49-6b1b6842e963.html |accessdate=17 July 2018 |work=The Roanoke Times |date=Mar 17, 2018}}</ref> |nationality = |fields = Computer Science, [[Digital currencies]] | alma_mater = |known_for = [[EOS (cryptocurrency)|EOS]], [[Steemit]], and BitShares |author_abbrev_bot = |author_abbrev_zoo = |influences = |influenced = |awards = |religion = |signature = <!--(filename only)--> |footnotes = |website = https://bytemaster.github.io }}
'''Daniel Larimer''' is a software programmer and [[cryptocurrency]] entrepreneur. Larimer created the cryptocurrency platform BitShares (2014), was co-founder of the blockchain social platform [[Steemit]] (2016), and is CTO Block.one, a private company that was the original developer of [[EOS (cryptocurrency)|EOS]] (2017).<ref name="CryptCoin1">{{cite web|url=https://cryptocoin.news/news/ethereum/dan-larimer-creator-of-the-fastest-blockchains-now-targeting-sub-second-latency-in-eos-2577/|title=Dan Larimer, Creator Of The Fastest Blockchains, Now Targeting Sub-second Latency In EOS|work=Cryptocoin.news|date=October 8, 2017}}</ref><ref name="forbes">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jeffkauflin/2018/02/07/fintech-crypto-billionaires-dan-larimer|title=Dan Larimer's Path From Working On Weapons To Minting Crypto Riches|first=Jeff|last=Kauflin|work=Forbes|date=Feb 7, 2018}}</ref> Daniel Larimer was also the creator of the DPOS (Delegated Proof of Stake Algorithm) consensus algorithm and Graphene technology. In February 2018, Forbes estimated Larimer's net worth between $600 to $700 million.<ref name="forbes" />
==Personal life== Dan Larimer's father is Stan Larimer, who worked for [[Boeing]], and with whom he founded Cryptonomex Inc., a blockchain technology consulting business.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/rogeraitken/2015/10/12/meet-cryptonomexs-dan-larimer-and-his-four-horsemen-of-crypto-economics|work=Forbes|year=2015|title=Meet Cryptonomex's Dan Larimer And His 'Four Horsemen' Of Crypto-Economics}}</ref> He received his Bachelor of Science (BS) in Computer Science from [[Virginia Polytechnic Institute and State University]] in 2003.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bytemaster.github.io/about/|title=Daniel Larimer - A Passion for Freedom via Decentralization}}</ref> After launching a [[virtual reality]] startup that failed, he worked in the [[Arms industry|defense]], [[robotics]] and [[automation]] industries.<ref name="forbes" /> His interest in [[blockchain]]s began in 2009, in the early days of [[Bitcoin]].<ref name="CryptCoin1"/><ref name="roanoke" />
==Endeavors== Larimer developed the blockchain technology Graphene, which powers BitShares and the Steem token cryptocurrency.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://medium.com/@mohitsingh_54387/the-wizard-behind-bitshares-steem-eos-how-dan-larimer-is-shaping-our-future-d9233ec634a7|title=The Wizard behind Bitshares, Steem & EOS - How Dan Larimer is shaping our future|last=Singh |first=Mohit|date=5 July 2017|access-date=1 November 2018}}</ref>
